<h1>@HI{{to @KJ{{say}}tte imashita}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @Splain{{}} @HI{{@EM{{to @KJ{{say}}tte imashita}}}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
This pattern is used to convey the words of a third person.
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{rice*field^in}}sanha ashita @KJ{{rest}}mu@EM{{to @KJ{{say}}tte imashita}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Mr. Tanaka said that he would take a day off tomorrow.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
The related pattern @HI{{to iimashita}} is used to quote a third person's words.
</p>

